  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="KT235-kilavi">
        <p type="edition">varaiyātu pirintu varuvāṉ vāṭaikku uraippāṉāyp pākaṟku uraittatu. </p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Told to the charioteer as if telling the north wind, by
          him who is coming after having separated without marrying. </p>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="KT235">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l> ōmpumati vāḻiyō vāṭai pāmpiṉ</l>
          <l> ṟūṅkutōl kaṭukkun tūveḷ ḷaruvik</l>
          <l> kalluyar naṇṇi yatuvē nelli</l>
          <l> maraiyiṉa māru muṉṟiṟ</l>
          <l> pulvēy kurampai nallō ḷūrē.</l>
        </lg>

        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
          <l>Live, north wind, beware</l>
          <l rend="indent2">of the village with grass-thatched huts of the good <note place="foot">
              <term xml:lang="ta">nal</term> , as so often, is problematic as an attribute here.
            Does it refer to her outer appearance, that is, "good" in the sense of "lovely" or
            something similar? Does it refer to her social status, that is, she is acceptable in
            spite of obviously being poor?</note> woman</l>
          <l rend="indent2">[and] front-yards, where groups of wild cows feed</l>
          <l rend="indent8">on Nelli [fruits].</l>
          <l>It lies in stony height</l>
          <l rend="indent2">by the pure white waterfall, resembling the hanging slough</l>
          <l rend="indent8">of a snake.</l>

          <lg type="alternate" sameAs="1b">
            <l>Live, north wind, protect the village ...<note place="foot">This second alternative
              is Cām.'s choice. Probably both possibilities are intended: there are clear parallels
              with <term xml:lang="ta">ōmpu</term> in both senses (cf. KT 184, 206 – KT 223), among
              them a formulaic parallel of <term xml:lang="ta">ōmpumiṉ</term> in KT 184 which seems
              to justify the primary reading – which is especially interesting because it represents
              an unusual topos, the reckless and disturbing woman.</note>
            </l>
          </lg>
        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
